  "text": "In previous studies, it was reported that adriamycin injection led to a significant increase in the number of apoptotic podocytes followed by glomerulosclerosis in a rodent model [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, a DPP-IV inhibitor ameliorated diabetes-induced podocyte injury [CITATION_3] . Our study suggested that the effects of gemigliptin on oxidative stress and apoptosis prevent podocyte loss due to renal injury.",
